text: Warmi Mach'ay (Quechua warmi woman, mach'ay cave, "woman cave", Hispanicized spelling Huarmimachay) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is situated in the Huancavelica Region, Huancavelica Province, Acobambilla District, and in the Junín Region, Huancayo Province, Chongos Alto District. Warmi Mach'ay lies between the lakes named Warmiqucha in the southeast and Quylluqucha in the northwest. ==References== Category:Mountains of Huancavelica Region Category:Mountains of Junín Region Category:Mountains of Peru
